&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;Input&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;This is the target reference voltage. It is used to check if the target has power, to create the logic-level reference for the input comparators and to control the output logic levels to the target. It is normally fed from VDD of the target board and must not have a series resistor.&lt;/td&gt;
